==English==
===Etymology===
The name Juliet is present in two languages, which is Latin and French. In Latin it means "youthful" or "Jove's child." While in French it means "Soft-haired."

===Pronunciation===
''joo-lee-ET''

===Proper noun===
'''Juliet'''

#A female [[given name]].
#One of the [[main character]]s of [[w:William Shakespeare|William Shakespeare]]'s play ''[[w:Romeo and Juliet|Romeo and Juliet]]''.
#A woman who is or is with a great lover.
#By analogy of the Shakespearean character, a woman who is in love with a man from a family, party, or country opposing that of her own.
#The sixth [[moon]] of the [[planet]] [[Uranus]].

